        {
            "_id": "GUmXcN197bEojqp6",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Dread Gaze",
            "sort": 400000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>Voldrak fixes his gaze upon a creature he can see within 60 feet. His eyes glow with blue light, then begin to pulse, compelling the creature he views to remain motionless with fear. The target must attempt a @Check[will|dc:36|options:inflicts:frightened,inflicts:slowed,inflicts:paralyzed] save with the following effects. Voldrak can't use Dread Gaze again for [[/gmr 1d4 #Recharge Dread Gaze]]{1d4 rounds}.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected and is temporarily immune to Dread Gaze for 24 hours.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 1}.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature increases the value of its frightened condition by 1 (or becomes frightened 1 if not yet frightened). As long as the creature remains frightened, it is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 2}.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but as long as the creature remains frightened, it is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Paralyzed].</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
